<H2> KSP Manual Pages
[<A HREF="../manual.html#Node49"> Section 4.3 of Users Manual</A>]
</H2> 

To solve linear systems, users should employ the
<A HREF="man3.html">Scalable Linear Equations Solvers (SLES)</A>
component, which provides an easy-to-use interface to the combination of
a Krylov subspace iterative method and a preconditioner (in the KSP and
<A HREF="man4.html">PC</A>
components, respectively).  SLES users can set various Krylov
subspace options at runtime via the options database (e.g., 
<font face ="Courier">
-ksp_type cg
</font face>
).  
SLES users can also set KSP options directly in application
codes by first extracting the KSP context from the SLES context via
<A HREF="man3/SLESGetKSP.html">SLESGetKSP()</A>
and then directly calling the KSP routines listed below (e.g., 
<A HREF="man5/KSPSetType.html">KSPSetType()</A>
).
Both KSP and PC components can be used directly to create and
destroy solvers; this approach is not needed for most users but
rather is intended for library developers.

